Business Problem
Ad Operations teams handle a large volume of requests related to campaign trafficking, reporting, QA reviews, meetings, troubleshooting, and client support. Tracking these requests through spreadsheets often makes it difficult to:

Monitor overall workload across team members.
Identify peak request periods.
Measure individual trafficker and QA performance.
Analyze client-wise demand.
Understand operational bottlenecks.
Generate management-ready performance reports.

This dashboard addresses these challenges by providing real-time visibility into operational performance and workload patterns.

Data Sources
The dashboard utilizes data collected through an internal request-tracking system containing:

Request Date
Request Type
Client Name
Placement Count
Trafficker Name
QA Person
Number of Requests
Reporting Period
QA Status and Assignment Details

The data was cleaned, transformed, and modeled using Power Query and DAX to create meaningful business metrics.

Dashboard Components
1. Trafficking Performance Analysis
The first dashboard page focuses on request management and trafficking activities.
Key metrics include:

Placement count by month.
Placement distribution across traffickers.
Request volume by weekday.
Client-wise request contribution.
Detailed request-level data table.

This allows team leads and managers to understand:

Which traffickers are handling the highest volume.
Monthly workload fluctuations.
Peak operational periods.
High-demand clients requiring additional support.


2. QA Performance Analysis
The second dashboard page focuses on quality assurance activities.
Features include:

Monthly placement count reviewed by QA personnel.
QA workload distribution across team members.
QA contribution percentage analysis.
Client-wise QA request breakdown.
Detailed QA activity records.

The dashboard helps identify:

QA workload balancing opportunities.
Individual QA performance.
Clients generating the greatest QA effort.
Monthly QA demand trends.


Key Insights Generated
The dashboard enables users to identify:
Operational Trends

Wednesday shows the highest request volume compared to other weekdays.
March and June represent peak placement activity periods.
Workload varies significantly throughout the year.

Team Performance

Individual contribution of traffickers and QA personnel can be compared.
Resource allocation effectiveness becomes visible.
Workload concentration among specific team members can be identified.

Client Analysis

Clients such as Klaviyo and Wella contribute a significant portion of requests.
Client-level request patterns help forecast future operational demand.
High-volume accounts can be prioritized for resource allocation.

Process Visibility

Provides end-to-end visibility from request creation to QA completion.
Supports workload forecasting and capacity planning.
Reduces dependency on manual reporting.


